g3log
------------------------------------------
G3log is an asynchronous, 'crash safe', logger that is easy to use with
default logging sinks or you can add your own. G3log is made with plain C++11
with no external libraries (except gtest used for unit tests). G3log is made
to be cross-platform, currently running on OSX, Windows and several Linux
distros. See Readme below for details of usage.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.5-1
  libg3log-devel-2.6-1bl1
  libg3log2-2.6-1bl1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.45-1
  cmake-3.31.3-1
  cygport-0.37.3-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/KjellKod/g3log

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/KjellKod/g3log/archive/refs/tags/2.6.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack g3log-2.6-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./g3log-2.6-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/g3log-2.6-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/g3log-2.6-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libg3log2-2.6-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libg3log-devel-2.6-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

